### Create Direct Consent (Tablet Flow)
POST http://localhost:8085/admin/consents
Content-Type: application/json
X-Tenant-ID: salon-uuid-123

{
  "subject": "customer-uuid-123",
  "policies": [
    { "slug": "privacy-policy" },
    { "slug": "marketing-consent" }
  ]
}

### Create Consent with Specific Version
POST http://localhost:8085/admin/consents
Content-Type: application/json
X-Tenant-ID: salon-uuid-123

{
  "subject": "customer-uuid-456",
  "policies": [
    { "slug": "privacy-policy", "version": "1.0.0" }
  ]
}

### Get All Consents for a Subject
GET http://localhost:8085/admin/consents?subject=customer-uuid-123
X-Tenant-ID: salon-uuid-123

### Get Specific Policy Consent for Subject
GET http://localhost:8085/admin/consents?subject=customer-uuid-123&policy=privacy-policy
X-Tenant-ID: salon-uuid-123

### Get Consent by ID
# Replace with actual consent ID
GET http://localhost:8085/admin/consents/consent-id-here
X-Tenant-ID: salon-uuid-123

### Revoke Consent
# Replace with actual consent ID
DELETE http://localhost:8085/admin/consents/consent-id-here
Content-Type: application/json
X-Tenant-ID: salon-uuid-123

{
  "revoked_by": "operator-123"
}

### Get Consent Status - All policies for a subject
# Returns: accepted, missing, or outdated for each requested policy
GET http://localhost:8085/admin/consents/status?subject=customer-uuid-123&slugs=privacy-policy,marketing-consent
X-Tenant-ID: salon-uuid-123

### Get Consent Status - Single policy
GET http://localhost:8085/admin/consents/status?subject=customer-uuid-123&slugs=privacy-policy
X-Tenant-ID: salon-uuid-123

### Get Consent Status - Subject with no consents (all missing)
GET http://localhost:8085/admin/consents/status?subject=new-customer-uuid&slugs=privacy-policy,marketing-consent
X-Tenant-ID: salon-uuid-123
